title: V for Vendetta: Vol 1-3 (of 3|DC|1988-89|theProletariat-DCP-HD)
description:
To be clear, this is the entirety of "V for Vendetta" ( <a href=" http://en.wikipedia.org/wi..." rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://en.wikipedia.org/wi...</a>  nah, on second thought, there's really no need for an expository link here, is there). The tale is organized by books and chapters as well as by issues, and both the former and the latter are occasionally designated as "volumes" (even within the text itself), which makes things a lot more confusing than they'd need to be.

Be that as it may, this tripartite* approach is certainly the most organic, says I.

Compiled from theProletariat's superb traditionally scanned 10-issue re-release ( <a href=" http://thepiratebay.se/torrent/7571137" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://thepiratebay.se/torrent/7571137</a>  ), and bookended with a couple of TPB covers and pinups which I discovered just now and which prompted me to post this.

---
* Semanteme selected solely so as to satisfy STFmv's sesquipedalophilia - for sooth!
